      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Glowy foundation",
          "reviewText": "You know what, this is really a nice foundation. Not too thick and not too heavy. Kind of melts on your face. Wears well. And you can't tell I'm wearing foundation. Leaves a nice glow too. I really like this foundation. Great dupe for Natasha Denona and the color match was much better.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2026",
          "customer": "Susan N. Krubl",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFTJZFHT4RVPFHYOUS7XQTITJPSA",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "220 WARM"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "8 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Absolutely beautiful.",
          "reviewText": "This foundation is absolutely amazing and it has already become my favorite foundation out of all the ones I wear. I was skeptical to buy it because the reviews have been mixed. I think if you have oily skin, it seems that you probably won\u2019t like this one and apparently the shades are not that great, but for me personally , I have normal skin so this is absolutely beautiful on my mature skin. It feels so nice going on. It doesn\u2019t settle into any lines or wrinkles. It covers. It doesn\u2019t look like makeup and it doesn\u2019t feel like make up and the shade I got 118 does not oxidize on me. I did have to go down a few shades from my normal Maybelline shade numbers. I would recommend getting a shade 10 digits less than whatever you normally use in Maybelline fit me or Maybelline serum foundation.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2025",
          "customer": "Beth",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFO3J2S6SQO5BXTPYGXHZENEYBVQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "118 WARM"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "21 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Beautiful skin like finish not the coverage. A lot of women will need.",
          "reviewText": "It is a beautiful foundation with a soft, natural finish. The coverage is light to light-medium\u2014maybe close to medium\u2014but it doesn\u2019t build beyond that. I get about six hours of wear, which is decent, but it doesn\u2019t last a full day for me . I\u2019m 52 with slight rosacea and normal skin, I needed a bit more coverage and staying power. If you have good skin and want a fresh, skin-like look, this would be lovely. If you need fuller coverage or all-day wear, it may not be the best fit.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2026",
          "customer": "C. M.",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFZM42NW7A4NZKBZEXJFSU7HV62Q",
          "customerStarsRating": 4,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "118 WARM"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "13 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Skin like foundation",
          "reviewText": "I been looking for a foundation for my combination skin. I also don\u2019t like makeup that is heavy on my skin. This foundation is like my skin while covering my blemishes. A co-worker asked why my skin was glowing. This foundation is buildable but I like to have a thin layer and I still have \u201cgreat skin\u201d after all day of wearing it. My work requires a mask and this foundation stayed on longer than my old one. Doesn\u2019t have that ugly dryness at the nose like other foundation.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on March 18, 2026",
          "customer": "Chau Tran",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEL6EM7MUEV272CJBXYNQKMYI2UQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "113 NEUTRAL"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "3 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "For a younger woman this is perfect. Four more mature women, not so much",
          "reviewText": "I have mature skin. I'm 59 years old, and I've tried dozens of foundations. This one is just kind of middle of the road. It does settle in my fine lines after it's been on for about an hour. I would recommend this for a younger woman. It is silky and smooth and I love that part of it but it just is not a great choice for an older woman.",
